snippet.textDisplay:
I think Phoenix’s performance is truly legendary. But for me, it’s message was kinda just presented completely at face value, there wasn’t any subtly or nuance to it. It felt sort of hammered into every scene so bluntly. Also, the third act felt so messy, it should have ended 20 minutes before it did (when he shot the guy) but everything after that absolutely lost the pacing and veered away from said message.

It absolutely deserved Best Actor nom but definitely not writing or directing.
snippet.textOriginal:
I think Phoenix’s performance is truly legendary. But for me, it’s message was kinda just presented completely at face value, there wasn’t any subtly or nuance to it. It felt sort of hammered into every scene so bluntly. Also, the third act felt so messy, it should have ended 20 minutes before it did (when he shot the guy) but everything after that absolutely lost the pacing and veered away from said message.

It absolutely deserved Best Actor nom but definitely not writing or directing.
